.TH "fsl_mc_object_allocate" 9 "fsl_mc_object_allocate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_mc_object_allocate \- Allocates an fsl-mc object of the given pool type from a given fsl-mc bus instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_mc_object_allocate
.BI "(struct fsl_mc_device *mc_dev "  ","
.BI "enum fsl_mc_pool_type pool_type "  ","
.BI "struct fsl_mc_device **new_mc_adev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mc_dev" 12
fsl-mc device which is used in conjunction with the
allocated object
.IP "pool_type" 12
pool type
.IP "new_mc_adev" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocatable objects are always used in conjunction with some functional
device.  This function allocates an object of the specified type from
the DPRC containing the functional device.
.SH "NOTE"
pool_type must be different from FSL_MC_POOL_MCP, since MC
portals are allocated using \fBfsl_mc_portal_allocate\fP, instead of
this function.
